<paragraph id="8BE5FB4F101FFFAAFF64FEC3799E56ED" blockId="8.[136,1452,266,760]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFF64FEC37947555D" bold="true" box="[189,265,302,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Notes:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFECAFEC279C8555D" box="[275,390,303,328]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFECAFEC279C8555D" box="[275,390,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Beauveria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFD4AFEC37BE6555C" author="Balsamo-Crivelli, G." box="[659,936,302,329]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="125" refId="ref8511" refString="Balsamo-Crivelli, G. (1835) Osservazione sopra una nuova spezie di Mucedinea del genere Botrytis. Biblioteca di Bibliografia Italiana 79: 125." type="journal article" year="1835">Balsamo-Crivelli (1835)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFC08FEC27CD0555D" box="[977,1182,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFC08FEC27CD7555D" box="[977,1177,302,328]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Sclerotiniaceae" genus="Botrytis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">Botrytis bassiana</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but later the name was changed to 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFEC8FEBE79B45579" box="[273,506,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFEC8FEBE79BB5579" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="Balsamo-Crivelli" box="[273,501,338,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">Beauveria bassiana</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and it was assigned as the 
<typeStatus id="54E145ED101FFFAAFC9DFEBE7B3A5578" box="[836,884,339,365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">type</typeStatus>
species of new independent genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFACEFEBE7DC45579" box="[1303,1418,339,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFACEFEBE7DC45579" box="[1303,1418,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Beauveria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFF51FE9B790F5585" box="[136,321,374,400]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Cordycipitaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFE92FE9B7A965585" authority="(Paul Vuillemin 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Paul Vuillemin" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[331,728,374,400]" class="Sordariomycetes" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">
Hypocreales (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFE3CFE9B7A9E5585" author="Paul Vuillemin, M." box="[485,720,374,400]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="34 - 40" refId="ref13613" refString="Paul Vuillemin, M. (1912) Beauveria, nouveau genre de Verticilliacees. Bulletin de la societe botanique de france 59: 34 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00378941.1912.10832379" type="journal article" year="1912">Paul Vuillemin 1912</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This genus was characterized asexually by having globose bases and extended denticulate rachis, unicellular, ball-like, holoblastic conidia (&lt;3.5 μm diam) formed on globose to flaskshaped phialide conidiogenous cells (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFDF1FE537AA955CD" author="Costa, E. M. D. &amp; Pimenta, F. C. &amp; Luz, C. &amp; Oliveira, V. D. &amp; Oliveira, M. &amp; Bueno, E. &amp; Petrofeza, S." box="[552,743,446,472]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="12 - 21" refId="ref9498" refString="Costa, E. M. D., Pimenta, F. C., Luz, C., Oliveira, V. D., Oliveira, M., Bueno, E. &amp; Petrofeza, S. (2011) Beauveria bassiana: quercetinase production and genetic diversity. Brazilian Journal of Microbiology 42: 12 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 1517 - 83822011000100002" type="journal article" year="2011">
Costa 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFDB6FE527AE955CD" box="[623,679,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFD28FE537BE255CD" author="Chen, M. J. &amp; Huang, B. &amp; Li, Z. Z. &amp; Spatafora, J. W." box="[753,940,446,472]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="301 - 308" refId="ref9186" refString="Chen, M. J., Huang, B., Li, Z. Z., Spatafora, J. W. (2013) Morphological and genetic characterisation of Beauveria sinensis sp. nov. from China. Mycotaxon 124: 301 - 308. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 124.301" type="journal article" year="2013">
Chen 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFCEAFE527B2455CD" box="[819,874,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
), whereas the sexual morphs produce solitary, paired or gregarious stromata, cylindrical to clavate, yellowish to orange, cylindrical and filiform ascospores (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFA84FE0F79465635" author="Kepler, R. M. &amp; Hywel-Jones, N. L. &amp; Quandt, C. A. &amp; Sung, G. H. &amp; Rehner, S. A. &amp; Aime, M. C. &amp; Henkel, T. W. &amp; Sanjuan, T. &amp; Zare, R. &amp; Chen, M. &amp; Li, Z. &amp; Rossman, A. Y. &amp; Spatafora, J. W. &amp; Shrestha, B." pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="335 - 353" refId="ref12137" refString="Kepler, R. M., Luangsa-ard, J. J., Hywel-Jones, N. L., Quandt, C. A., Sung, G. H., Rehner, S. A., Aime, M. C., Henkel, T. W., Sanjuan, T., Zare, R., Chen, M., Li, Z., Rossman, A. Y., Spatafora, J. W. &amp; Shrestha, B. (2017) A phylogenetically-based nomenclature for Cordycipitaceae (Hypocreales). IMA Fungus 8: 335 - 353. https: // doi. org / 10.5598 / imafungus. 2017.08.02.08" type="journal article" year="2017">
Kepler 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFF51FDEA788C5635" box="[136,194,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFEC5FDEA79B25635" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="Balsamo-Crivelli" box="[284,508,518,544]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFEC5FDEA79B25635" box="[284,508,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Beauveria bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported as a pathogen of silkworms as early as 900 AD in 
<collectingCountry id="F34DBBDF101FFFAAFAC2FDEA7D105634" box="[1307,1374,519,545]" name="Japan" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and it was documented that the pathogen resulted in serious silkworm disease in 
<collectingCountry id="F34DBBDF101FFFAAFC0EFDC77C445651" box="[983,1034,554,580]" name="Italy" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Italy</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F34DBBDF101FFFAAFB9AFDC67CC15650" box="[1091,1167,555,581]" name="France" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">France</collectingCountry>
around 1800 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFAECFDC778A7567D" author="Samson, R. A. &amp; Evans, H. C. &amp; Latge, J. P." pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="703 - 705" refId="ref14161" refString="Samson, R. A., Evans, H. C. &amp; Latge, J. P. (2013) Atlas of entomopathogenic fungi. Springer Science &amp; Business Media. pp. 703 - 705." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Samson 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFA4EFDC678EB567D" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). However, some 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFE76FDA27A19567C" box="[431,599,591,617]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE76FDA27A6C567D" box="[431,546,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Beauveria</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
also were reported as endophytes or saprobes associated with various plants (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFF56FD9F79025699" author="Vega, F. E. &amp; Posada, F. &amp; Aime, M. C. &amp; Pava-Ripoll, M. &amp; Infante, F. &amp; Rehner, S. A." box="[143,332,626,652]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="72 - 82" refId="ref15007" refString="Vega, F. E., Posada, F., Aime, M. C., Pava-Ripoll, M., Infante, F. &amp; Rehner, S. A. (2008) Entomopathogenic fungal endophytes. Biological Control 46: 72 - 82. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. biocontrol. 2008.01.008" type="journal article" year="2008">
Vega 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFF08FD9E79445699" box="[209,266,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFE8EFD9F7A095699" author="Moonjely, S. &amp; Barelli, L. &amp; Bidochka, M. J." box="[343,583,626,652]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="107 - 135" refId="ref12869" refString="Moonjely, S., Barelli, L. &amp; Bidochka, M. J. (2016) Insect pathogenic fungi as endophytes. Advances in Genetics 94: 107 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / bs. adgen. 2015.12.004" type="journal article" year="2016">
Moonjely 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE15FD9E7A4B5699" box="[460,517,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
, Imoulana 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFD1DFD9E7AB35699" box="[708,765,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2017, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFC93FD9F7C465699" author="Chen, W. H. &amp; Liu, M. &amp; Huang, Z. X. &amp; Yang, G. M. &amp; Han, Y. F. &amp; Liang, J. D. &amp; Liang, Z. Q." box="[842,1032,626,652]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="243 - 250" refId="ref9307" refString="Chen, W. H., Liu, M., Huang, Z. X., Yang, G. M., Han, Y. F., Liang, J. D. &amp; Liang, Z. Q. (2018) Beauveria majiangensis, a new entomopathogenic fungus from Guizhou, China. Phytotaxa 333: 243 - 250. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 333.2.8" type="journal article" year="2018">
Chen 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFC54FD9E7B885699" box="[909,966,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFBCDFD9F7D455699" author="Khonsanit, A. &amp; Thanakitpipattana, D. &amp; Noisripoom, W. &amp; Chaitika, T. &amp; Kobmoo, N." box="[1044,1291,626,652]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="291 - 315" refId="ref12427" refString="Khonsanit, A., Luangsa-ard, J. J., Thanakitpipattana, D., Noisripoom, W., Chaitika, T. &amp; Kobmoo, N. (2020) Cryptic diversity of the genus Beauveria with a new species from Thailand. Mycological Progress 19: 291 - 315. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 020 - 01557 - 9" type="journal article" year="2020">
Khonsanit 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFB57FD9E7C895699" box="[1166,1223,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFAC7FD9E7DDF5699" box="[1310,1425,627,652]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFAC7FD9E7DDF5699" box="[1310,1425,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Beauveria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread anamorphic genus of entomopathogenic fungi, which includes ecologically and economically important species, for example, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFE5AFD567A4756C1" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="Balsamo-Crivelli" box="[387,521,698,724]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE5AFD567A4756C1" box="[387,521,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">B. bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely utilized as a biological pest control agent in agriculture (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFAC8FD57788D56ED" author="Zimmermann, G." pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="553 - 596" refId="ref15705" refString="Zimmermann, G. (2007) Review on safety of the entomopathogenic fungi Beauveria bassiana and Beauveria brongniartii. Biocontrol Science and Technology 17: 553 - 596. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09583150701309006" type="journal article" year="2007">Zimmermann 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFF17FD33798A56ED" author="Khonsanit, A. &amp; Thanakitpipattana, D. &amp; Noisripoom, W. &amp; Chaitika, T. &amp; Kobmoo, N." box="[206,452,734,760]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="291 - 315" refId="ref12427" refString="Khonsanit, A., Luangsa-ard, J. J., Thanakitpipattana, D., Noisripoom, W., Chaitika, T. &amp; Kobmoo, N. (2020) Cryptic diversity of the genus Beauveria with a new species from Thailand. Mycological Progress 19: 291 - 315. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 020 - 01557 - 9" type="journal article" year="2020">
Khonsanit 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE91FD3279CE56ED" box="[328,384,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
